Reasoning: The paper presents two new algorithms for solving the All Pairs Shortest Paths problem for weighted directed graphs using fast matrix multiplication algorithms. This problem is a fundamental problem in computer science and can be applied in various fields such as network routing, transportation planning, and social network analysis. The use of matrix multiplication algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category as it deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The use of numerical methods and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category as it deals with the running time analysis of the algorithms presented.
